    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[GrYa68] Graver, Jack E. and Yackel, James, Some graph theoretic results associated with Ramsey's theorem. J. Combinatorial Theory (1968), 125--175.",
      "remarks": "The function $h_3(k)$ is dual to the function $f(n)$ considered in [1104], in that $h_3(k)= n$ if and only if $n$ is minimal such that $f(n)=k$.\n\nGraver and Yackel \\cite{GrYa68} proved\\[h_3(k)\\gg \\frac{\\log k}{\\log\\log k}k^2.\\]The bounds for $f(n)$ from [1104] imply\\[\\left(\\frac{1}{2}-o(1)\\right)k^2\\log k\\leq h_3(k) \\leq (1+o(1))k^2\\log k.\\]See also [920] for a generalisation to $K_r$-free graphs."
    },
    "source_state": "open",
    "tags": [
      "graph theory"
    ]
  },
